reviews.text: Nice quite place. Nice staff. Good attentive service. I had the Lunch Special Lobster Roll, but I did not like it. Other than that everything else was good. Be sure you keep an eye on your parking meter outside.

Excellent food and service. The menu has a nice variety of Japanese and Thai dishes to choose from. All of the food tastes fresh, and is presented in a lovely way. The servers are all really nice and helpful with suggestions on what to order. It's a nice little restaurant, modern, clean, and cozy. It's quickly becoming one of our favorites!
Absolutely fantastic! Excellent food. Great selection of dishes. Incredible presentation. Reasonable prices. Plentiful portioned plates. This is a must-visit restaurant.

We were looking for somewhere quick near an upcoming appointment that was not fast food. My niece and I were seated right away and ordered within three minutes. Less than ten minutes later we were enjoying delicious lunch specials. The portion size was more than fair for the great lunch price.

I met and chatted with Will, one of the chef/owners over lunch today.  Very nice, approachable dude.  The atmosphere was relaxed.  The food was beautifully presented, perfectly fresh, delicious and fairly priced.  Will be returning.

Very reasonable 10 Euro for an audio tour of the palace. I would highly recommend to anyone! There are kids audio options and if you are really interested in something you can get even more information via audio. The staff are SUPER friendly and there is a cloakroom for your bag and coats.

Beautiful palace that just inspires awe at every turn. To be among such great pieces of work and history is truly humbling.

This place is very befitting of the title "Royal" and is a marvel with the intricacies of the paintings, sculptures, and works of art scattered throughout.

The admission is fairly priced and comes with a free audio tour that provides nuggets of information on the various rooms and history associated with them. Additionally, the tour gives you options of learning the extra facts relating to a sculpture and/or painting.

I really feel like you could come here 2 or 3 times and still learn or see something new here. Absolutely beautiful in hundreds of ways, witnessing this building and all its treasures firsthand is something spectacular. Pictures don't do it justice.

Anything to do with Amsterdam is already good enough for me. Add to that a chance to take in the Royal Palace, the cherry has been placed on my tourism cake. 

Taking a walking tour was well worth it. We learned so much from our guide, it truly made the experience memorable.

If you have the time, why not do it? The architecture that surrounds the area alone, is well worth it.

First of all, if you're into interesting buildings, you can never go wrong with palaces. This type of buildings are always the place of many interesting stories. This city hall turned palace during the reign of Napoleon is no different. Large halls full of exquisite art and the most expensive furniture give you a peek at how it is to be a dignitary in the Netherlands. The excellent audio tour (with a special version for kids) in a dozen languages that allows you to wander through the halls in your own tempo makes it a five star to visit. No rush, just interesting history.

It’s amazing that you’re able to walk in and explore the actual Royal Palace! There’s a wide range of different rooms - all with unique snippets of history attached. Joy for the whole family - would definitely recommend visiting it if you’re in Amsterdam.

Unlike many other sightseeing places, this one is very kid- and English-friendly. Kids get their own audio guide and a little necklace to fill out to keep them interested. For adults there are various language available - including English.
For me, this is the best museum in Europe. So many fantastic works of art.
Don't waste your time. The gallery is almost empty. Go to the national museum.
Short and sweet narrative of Bangkok fine arts.
Great exhibition. Especially, Marsis great paintings.
Definitely worth a visit! Intriguing artwork, and I think I literally spent hours there.
Really good sushi. Probably the best sushi I ever had outside Japan. Really traditional not only in the taste but also in the location. Remember to book!

Their sushi, atmosphere, service and especially their sashimi are ten out of ten heavenly perfect, only the karaage could have been a tiny bit better because of slightly soft skin and tiny pieces of tendons inside the meat
Used to go to this restaurant back in 2006. Still as good as it was. Feels and tastes like a restaurant in Japan.
Great food and service. Super small with cozy atmosphere.
Super nice, fair price. Really traditional not posh

As silver member got free upgrade to junior suite. One of the best suites i've been to. On 11 floor with balcony to the sea and great view on the city. Breakfast is also good with big variety. Recommend.
Awesome hotel. Really clean, well laid out rooms. The staff are all friendly, professional and helpful. Breakfast is amazing and the bar serves good food throughout the day. Highly recommend!

Very good location, clean rooms, very good breakfast.. There is a cosy lobby bar with friendly staff.
Fitness room is very small and hot water gets cold sometimes..
Location wise it gets all the 5 stars. Pretty clean. Friendly staff. Decent breakfast and lovely breakfast lounge. Ideally I would want a room with a view of the Caspian.
Stayed here for 1 night new years eve. Room was comfortable and clean. Located walking distance from the mall and restaurants
